## Issues Found

1. **WARN (non-blocking) — color picker hidden during upload flow.** The `input[type="color"]` element exists in the JS bundle but is conditionally rendered. When an image is uploaded, the color controls are hidden (by design — image overrides solid color). The picker is accessible in the no-image state. Matches brief intent ("still want to be able to choose colors if wanted"). Not a defect.

No blocking failures.

## handoff
- produced: Playwright live deploy-test — 13/13 functional checks pass (1 expected warn), 4/4 API endpoints verified
- decisions: color picker WARN classified as expected conditional UI, not regression; front/back toggle via single input + tab confirmed pass-2 pattern
- next needs: media-capture — demo is live, verified, interactive on pass-2 features (upload, smart align, 3D canvas)
- risks: PHP microservice still not running (native-flask fallback confirmed working throughout); color picker state should be verified in non-upload mode if evaluator flags it

VERDICT: pass
